docs.abstract: When the virus forced New York theater to go dark, it upended thousands of lives, from actors to ticket takers. An anatomy of one production.
docs.snippet: When the virus forced New York theater to go dark, it upended thousands of lives, from actors to ticket takers. An anatomy of one production.
docs.lead_paragraph: Seven months ago, on a brisk Thursday in March, New York’s theater world came to a sudden halt. Lives were upended, fortunes evaporated, dreams put on hold. Why do people come to New York, if not for some version of the dream embodied by theater: to experience the new, the fantastic, the tragic — some to witness, some to participate in its creation?

headline.main: Their Buzzy Off Broadway Play Shut Down. Here’s What They Did Next.
